WEBVTT

00:06.269 --> 00:07.789
CLARY: <i> Previously,
on</i> Shadowhunters...

00:08.384 --> 00:10.317
You must still have
feelings for her, huh?

00:10.345 --> 00:11.540
- (THUD)
- Shut up!

00:11.560 --> 00:12.759
Jace, what is going on?

00:12.908 --> 00:14.674
I'm not your brother, Clary.

00:14.757 --> 00:16.923
Now, my boy,
you are about to find out

00:17.326 --> 00:20.260
what it means to be a Herondale.

00:20.295 --> 00:21.583
That agony rune...

00:21.617 --> 00:23.583
(SCREAMING)

00:23.720 --> 00:26.174
made me relive memories
I've spent centuries

00:26.295 --> 00:27.260
trying to forget.

00:27.296 --> 00:28.528
(BOTH SCREAMING): Mama!

00:28.564 --> 00:30.230
Tell me how to fix this.

00:30.265 --> 00:31.298
Any last words?

00:31.333 --> 00:32.365
(EXHALING HEAVILY)

00:33.335 --> 00:34.367
(GRUNTING)

00:35.504 --> 00:37.304
Anyone else want to take a shot?
Come on!

00:37.339 --> 00:38.371
He's a daylighter...

00:38.407 --> 00:39.439
Damn right I am.

00:40.609 --> 00:44.311
(UPBEAT INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC)

00:44.346 --> 00:45.512
OK.

00:45.547 --> 00:47.247
Open.

00:49.618 --> 00:51.618
I...
kind of booked a show for you.

00:51.653 --> 00:54.254
O... K.

00:54.289 --> 00:57.190
Clary, this...
this is amazing. But...

00:57.226 --> 00:58.670
Rock Solid Panda's
kind of extinct now.

00:58.694 --> 01:01.495
There's no Rock. There's no solid.
I'm just a...

01:01.530 --> 01:03.296
a lone panda.

01:03.332 --> 01:05.364
I've heard the music you're writing.
It's...

01:05.400 --> 01:06.633
it's incredible.

01:06.674 --> 01:09.567
It'll be fine!
You can rock solid on your own.

01:09.600 --> 01:11.483
No. See, it's one thing
to jam in the boat basin.

01:11.507 --> 01:13.507
It's another thing to...

01:13.542 --> 01:17.544
play here. In front of...
actual people.

01:17.579 --> 01:19.379
Well, I...
I'm not an actual person?

01:19.414 --> 01:21.281
- No. Not at all.
- No?

01:21.316 --> 01:23.383
You're like...
on a totally different plane.

01:23.418 --> 01:25.418
I'll take that as a compliment.

01:29.258 --> 01:32.526
MAIA: It'd be cute if it wasn't so...
constant.

01:32.561 --> 01:34.561
Nope. Not even then.

01:34.596 --> 01:36.596
Must especially suck for you.

01:36.632 --> 01:38.365
Why?

01:39.635 --> 01:42.235
MAIA CHUCKLING: So...

01:42.264 --> 01:45.011
this rumor about you actually
being Shadowhunter royalty.

01:45.078 --> 01:45.465
Is it true?

01:45.479 --> 01:47.337
I don't know. Can it get me free
drinks at the Hunter's Moon?

01:47.361 --> 01:48.427
Let's not get crazy.

01:48.475 --> 01:49.738
(CHUCKLING)

01:50.499 --> 01:51.631
I don't know what I am.

01:51.666 --> 01:52.877
I've had three different
last names in a summer.

01:52.901 --> 01:53.833
Now I'm a Herondale.

01:53.869 --> 01:56.436
All I know is I'm the same Jace.

01:56.471 --> 01:57.537
God help us.

01:57.572 --> 01:59.539
Shot of Tequila. Double.

02:00.542 --> 02:02.542
Make that two.
Her shots are on me.

02:02.577 --> 02:03.877
Hey Kaelie.

02:03.912 --> 02:05.478
Long time.

02:05.514 --> 02:06.579
Thank you.

02:14.456 --> 02:15.755
(LAUGHING)

02:15.791 --> 02:20.427
Man, rejection is so much more
fun when it's happening to you.

02:20.462 --> 02:22.022
Hey, you don't make a lot of
tips, huh?

02:23.799 --> 02:25.565
Word of advice?

02:25.600 --> 02:27.834
I'd spare the Downworld
your charm for a little bit.

02:27.869 --> 02:30.837
That Soul Sword you ignited
killed a whole lot of them.

02:30.872 --> 02:33.907
<i>♪</i>

02:33.942 --> 02:37.444
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATION)

02:38.814 --> 02:42.549
<i>♪</i>

02:42.584 --> 02:44.551
- Hey.
Let's get out of here, - yeah?

02:44.586 --> 02:45.718
Yeah.

02:45.754 --> 02:48.555
<i>♪</i>

02:51.760 --> 02:53.460
SIMON: What if they
hate my music so bad

02:53.495 --> 02:54.806
that they start throwing
their pretzel sticks at me?

02:54.830 --> 02:56.774
CLARY: I'll take them down
before they get the chance.

02:56.798 --> 02:59.499
You're gonna be fine, Simon.

03:00.769 --> 03:01.634
What's wrong?

03:01.670 --> 03:03.536
I smell blood.

03:08.677 --> 03:09.742
CLARY: Ugh!

03:09.778 --> 03:11.644
Oh my God, that looks like...

03:11.680 --> 03:12.680
Human flesh.

03:12.714 --> 03:14.647
Simon, that's a rune.

03:15.650 --> 03:16.716
(METAL SCRAPING)

03:29.865 --> 03:32.732
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

03:32.767 --> 03:35.702
<i>♪ We're coming ♪</i>

03:35.737 --> 03:37.370
<i>♪</i>

03:37.405 --> 03:39.372
<i>♪ After you ♪</i>

03:39.407 --> 03:42.709
<i>♪ This is the hunt ♪</i>

03:42.744 --> 03:48.152
<i>♪</i>

03:48.750 --> 03:51.518
<i>♪ This is the hunt ♪</i>

03:51.553 --> 03:52.719
<i>♪</i>

03:52.754 --> 03:54.787
(ELECTRONIC WHIRRING)

03:54.823 --> 03:58.725
(FOOTSTEPS)

03:58.760 --> 04:00.527
Heard from Mom.
Max is on his way.

04:00.562 --> 04:01.562
Feels like just yesterday

04:01.596 --> 04:03.396
we were taking
knives away from him.

04:03.431 --> 04:04.509
Well he's lucky to
have you as a tutor.

04:04.533 --> 04:07.433
Alec. Maybe it's a mistake
putting me in charge of him.

04:07.469 --> 04:08.501
Are you kidding?

04:08.537 --> 04:10.436
Izzy,
you're the smartest one here.

04:10.472 --> 04:11.809
You're one of our
toughest fighters.

04:11.833 --> 04:14.389
But it's just...
I don't totally feel like myself yet.

04:14.476 --> 04:16.442
What about those
mundane meetings.

04:16.478 --> 04:17.510
They're helping...

04:17.546 --> 04:19.646
even though they think
I'm talking about heroin.

04:19.680 --> 04:21.714
JACE: Shadowhunter down.

04:21.750 --> 04:23.516
- CLARY: Milo Keytower.
- What happened?

04:23.552 --> 04:25.685
From what I understand,
his runes were carved out.

04:25.720 --> 04:26.653
Is that true, Jace?

04:26.688 --> 04:28.588
Yes. After he was
attacked by a wolf.

04:28.623 --> 04:29.901
He had multiple
bite and claw marks.

04:29.925 --> 04:32.625
What kind of werewolf randomly
attacks a Shadowhunter?

04:32.661 --> 04:33.871
One who's trying
to send a message.

04:33.895 --> 04:35.662
And get the attention
of the Clave.

04:35.697 --> 04:37.441
We need to find them
before this happens again.

04:37.465 --> 04:39.832
Well, I think I have a
pretty good idea who it is.

04:39.868 --> 04:41.601
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

04:41.636 --> 04:43.369
(METAL CLANKING)

04:43.838 --> 04:45.838
Really, Raphael?
Not tonight. Come on.

04:48.890 --> 04:51.678
Oh. You guys.

04:51.713 --> 04:53.713
Did Raphael send you
as some sort of threat?

04:53.748 --> 04:55.481
No. This isn't about Raphael.

04:55.517 --> 04:56.616
This is about you.

04:56.651 --> 04:58.718
We want to be in your clan.

04:58.753 --> 05:01.621
Uh... I don't have a clan.

05:01.656 --> 05:03.623
I'm a music major at NYU, so...

05:03.658 --> 05:05.391
For centuries,
we've heard the legend

05:05.427 --> 05:07.460
of how one day a great
leader would come.

05:07.495 --> 05:10.496
A vampire who can
walk in the daylight.

05:10.532 --> 05:14.434
We always thought it was...
a myth, folklore.

05:14.469 --> 05:16.636
You're proof that
the legends are true.

05:16.671 --> 05:18.805
Me? Me. Come on, guys.

05:18.840 --> 05:21.407
We're here for you.
Whatever you need, Daylighter.

05:21.443 --> 05:22.642
All you have to do is ask.

05:22.677 --> 05:24.577
Well, uh...

05:24.613 --> 05:26.879
Thank you.
I really appreciate it.

05:26.915 --> 05:29.515
But, uh... I'm good. So...

05:32.687 --> 05:34.654
Alright, look.
You guys seem really cool.

05:34.689 --> 05:36.623
For real. But, uh...

05:36.658 --> 05:39.359
I'm not really looking
for a posse at the moment.

05:39.394 --> 05:42.729
So, you guys should go
back and hang with Raphael.

05:42.764 --> 05:45.465
He's much more...

05:45.500 --> 05:48.735
you know, fit to be the
clan leader type, so...

05:52.741 --> 05:54.540
You know where to find us.

05:57.412 --> 05:58.811
(DOOR BELL JINGLING)

05:58.847 --> 06:00.780
SIMON: You know me, Luke.
I'm no leader,

06:00.815 --> 06:02.382
and I never have been!

06:02.417 --> 06:03.616
Don't sell yourself short.

06:03.652 --> 06:05.551
Not everybody can start
a band when they're 18.

06:05.587 --> 06:06.864
Well,
that band totally imploded.

06:06.888 --> 06:08.388
I mean,
you wanna meet my new band?

06:08.423 --> 06:09.389
'Cause you're
looking right at it!

06:09.424 --> 06:11.491
Look, all I want to do

06:11.526 --> 06:12.837
is go to college and hang
out with my girlfriend.

06:12.861 --> 06:13.861
Is that too much to ask?

06:13.895 --> 06:15.495
About that.

06:15.530 --> 06:18.765
I hope you and Clary are,
you know, being safe...

06:20.502 --> 06:21.834
Yeah. Yeah, um...

06:21.870 --> 06:25.471
totally. But I figured,
'cause of the vampire thing,

06:25.507 --> 06:27.707
I couldn't, um...

06:27.728 --> 06:29.943
I couldn't really get
Clary, you know...

06:29.949 --> 06:31.509
Whoa! Whoa! Whoa! Whoa!
Whoa! That's...

06:31.780 --> 06:33.446
I wasn't talking about that.

06:33.481 --> 06:35.648
I was talking about
the bloodlust.

06:35.684 --> 06:36.649
Right, yeah, of course!

06:36.685 --> 06:39.519
Well, if things get too heated

06:39.554 --> 06:40.420
I can, um...

06:40.455 --> 06:42.388
I know how to pull back.

06:42.424 --> 06:46.759
Uh, just... don't get overconfident.
I've seen

06:46.795 --> 06:49.696
it happen before.
You know, temptation and emotion...

06:49.731 --> 06:51.809
Can we please talk about any
other topic but this please?

06:51.833 --> 06:53.733
- Absolutely.
- ALEC: Luke, we need to talk.

06:53.768 --> 06:56.836
A Shadowhunter's been
mutilated and killed by a wolf.

06:56.871 --> 06:59.572
(THE BAR FALLS SILENT)

07:00.575 --> 07:01.507
Watch your tone in here.

07:01.543 --> 07:02.653
How do you know a
wolf killed him?

07:02.677 --> 07:04.815
Because of the claw marks and
traces of DNA on the body.

07:04.839 --> 07:07.557
Luke, the Inquisitor
would like you to come in.

07:08.650 --> 07:10.416
Just to answer a few questions.

07:10.452 --> 07:12.719
LUKE: Are you questioning
me or are you accusing me?

07:12.754 --> 07:16.489
A week ago, you demanded the
destruction of the Soul Sword.

07:16.524 --> 07:19.459
A demand which, of course,
is impossible to even consider.

07:19.494 --> 07:20.827
Which leads me to wonder...

07:20.862 --> 07:23.763
was this killing an act
of revenge on the Clave?

07:23.798 --> 07:25.810
LUKE SCOFFING: You think that
I would murder a Shadowhunter?

07:25.834 --> 07:28.501
We all know about your
temper, Lucian.

07:29.504 --> 07:30.581
Does she really
think Luke did this?

07:30.605 --> 07:31.504
LUKE: Take my DNA.

07:31.539 --> 07:32.839
Test it against your evidence.

07:32.874 --> 07:33.874
I'm not your wolf.

07:33.908 --> 07:35.708
And if any one of
my pack did it...

07:35.744 --> 07:37.543
I'll kill them myself.

07:40.849 --> 07:42.515
Take him down to the lab.

07:47.722 --> 07:48.722
A word, Jace?

07:51.559 --> 07:52.592
Luke didn't do this.

07:52.627 --> 07:54.761
I'm sure his DNA will prove it.

07:54.796 --> 07:56.729
That's the Herondale in you.

07:56.765 --> 07:59.465
We trust our gut
and act accordingly.

08:01.113 --> 08:02.702
You know, when your father died,

08:02.737 --> 08:05.605
I thought the Herondale
name would end with him.

08:05.640 --> 08:08.674
But by the grace of the
Angel, I was wrong.

08:08.710 --> 08:11.377
I see so much of
your father in you.

08:12.747 --> 08:14.380
But those eyes...

08:15.750 --> 08:17.650
those eyes you got
from your mother.

08:20.722 --> 08:22.388
What was she like?

08:22.424 --> 08:24.424
My mom.

08:24.459 --> 08:26.459
Celine was beautiful.

08:26.494 --> 08:28.661
Golden hair, like yours.

08:28.696 --> 08:30.430
She was so smart,

08:30.465 --> 08:32.532
so headstrong.

08:32.567 --> 08:34.767
You definitely got your
stubbornness from her.

08:36.538 --> 08:38.571
If they could see you
now, Jace...

08:38.606 --> 08:41.441
they would be so proud of you.

08:45.380 --> 08:47.580
I will be heading
back to Idris soon,

08:47.615 --> 08:50.683
and I will be appointing a
new Head of this Institute.

08:51.786 --> 08:53.519
It should be Alec.

08:53.555 --> 08:55.388
He's a born leader.

08:55.423 --> 08:56.700
There's no better
man for the job.

08:56.724 --> 09:00.493
Yes. Mr. Lightwood certainly is
one of our best and brightest.

09:00.528 --> 09:02.795
But I'm appointing you, Jace.

09:05.400 --> 09:06.766
Congratulations.

09:06.801 --> 09:08.501
It should've been you.
I told her that.

09:08.536 --> 09:10.216
The Clave was never
going to hand it to me.

09:10.772 --> 09:12.572
I'm dating a guy
who's a Downworlder.

09:12.607 --> 09:14.440
Look Alec, I didn't want
this, I swear.

09:14.476 --> 09:15.641
You're a Herondale.

09:15.677 --> 09:17.477
Get used to the perks.

09:17.512 --> 09:18.811
(ALARM RINGING)

09:18.847 --> 09:20.413
JACE: What happened?

09:20.448 --> 09:22.482
We found Rosegreen and
Penmount dead in the Bowery.

09:22.517 --> 09:23.483
Runes carved out.

09:23.518 --> 09:24.518
Just like Keytower.

09:24.552 --> 09:26.552
Except Penmount's been
drained by a vampire.

09:26.588 --> 09:28.688
And Rosegreen was lanced
by a Seelie Knight.

09:28.723 --> 09:30.835
It's not just a lone wolf.
It's multiple Downworlders.

09:30.859 --> 09:32.391
Luke was right all along.

09:32.427 --> 09:33.471
The Downworlders want revenge.

09:33.495 --> 09:34.638
This could be the
start of an uprising.

09:34.662 --> 09:36.762
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

09:36.798 --> 09:38.764
(WHEELS SQUEAKING)

09:41.503 --> 09:43.469
(FLUORESCENT LIGHT HUMMING)

09:43.505 --> 09:45.571
(HEAVY BREATHING)

09:45.607 --> 09:47.773
(WHIMPERING)

09:51.779 --> 09:54.714
(GRUNTING)

09:54.749 --> 09:55.848
Ah!

09:55.884 --> 09:58.751
(HEAVY BREATHING)

09:58.786 --> 10:00.620
(WHIMPERING)

10:00.655 --> 10:03.523
(SCISSORS SWISHING)

10:04.726 --> 10:06.659
(WHIMPERING)

10:06.694 --> 10:10.563
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

10:10.598 --> 10:13.466
(GRUNTING)

10:13.501 --> 10:14.567
(FLESH TEARING)

10:14.602 --> 10:16.602
(SCREAMING)

10:20.035 --> 10:22.897
HERONDALE: Another Shadowhunter
was found Dead last night

10:22.990 --> 10:26.519
in Williamsburg. This time,
murdered this time murdered by a warlock.

10:26.559 --> 10:29.626
In this time of
crisis, it is essential

10:29.676 --> 10:31.742
that we maintain
strong leadership.

10:31.778 --> 10:33.678
That is why I am naming.

10:33.713 --> 10:35.846
Jace Herondale Head
of the Institute,

10:35.882 --> 10:38.783
effective upon my
departure to Idris.

10:38.818 --> 10:40.718
Dismissed.

10:43.623 --> 10:44.900
Let's not make a
big deal about this.

10:44.924 --> 10:46.857
She's still in charge
until she leaves.

10:46.893 --> 10:49.493
IZZY: Still!
Being appointed Head of the Institute

10:49.529 --> 10:50.873
and finding out
you're a Herondale?

10:50.897 --> 10:51.829
Don't let it get to your head.

10:51.864 --> 10:52.908
CLARY: So Herondales are what,

10:52.932 --> 10:54.565
like the Kennedys
of the Shadow World?

10:54.601 --> 10:56.645
It's an old Shadowhunter family.
Like the Lightwoods.

10:56.669 --> 10:57.902
But we are the Kennedys.

10:57.937 --> 10:59.804
Let's focus on what matters.

10:59.839 --> 11:01.717
The Inquisitor would like us
to reach out to our allies,

11:01.741 --> 11:03.507
to see what they know.
At this point,

11:03.543 --> 11:05.476
she considers all
Downworlders suspects.

11:05.511 --> 11:06.822
That's casting a
pretty broad net.

11:06.846 --> 11:08.891
She can't possibly think
any of our friends did this.

11:08.915 --> 11:10.548
Yeah, well,
we'll prove that to her.

11:10.583 --> 11:12.750
Since Luke's DNA cleared him,
we should collect samples

11:12.785 --> 11:14.652
from all of our friends
to clear them as well.

11:14.687 --> 11:16.487
I'll make an Institute-wide
announcement.

11:16.522 --> 11:17.521
I'll go talk to Simon.

11:17.527 --> 11:18.397
Great. I'll go see Raphael.

11:18.437 --> 11:19.437
No.

11:20.693 --> 11:21.559
Why not?

11:21.594 --> 11:22.860
(SIGHING)

11:24.697 --> 11:26.697
Am I missing something here?

11:26.733 --> 11:29.600
Jace... I'm a Yin Fen addict.

11:29.636 --> 11:30.868
Excuse me?

11:30.903 --> 11:33.671
IZZY SIGHING: It's a long
story, but I'm better now.

11:33.706 --> 11:35.740
Not perfect, but better.

11:35.775 --> 11:38.643
Definitely good
enough to hunt down

11:38.678 --> 11:39.918
whoever's murdering our people.

11:42.515 --> 11:43.781
OK.

11:43.816 --> 11:45.650
We'll take all the
help we can get.

11:45.685 --> 11:47.618
Just report back with any
leads, OK?

11:48.921 --> 11:50.521
ALEC: I'm going with you.

11:50.556 --> 11:53.658
No. I'll have more traction
with Raphael if it's just me.

11:53.693 --> 11:55.726
I'll leave as soon
as Max is settled.

11:57.730 --> 11:59.463
Alec, I can handle this.

11:59.499 --> 12:01.432
You just have to trust me.

12:04.504 --> 12:06.437
(POLICE SIRENS)

12:07.874 --> 12:09.473
Alexander.

12:09.509 --> 12:11.909
Wow. You look very...

12:11.944 --> 12:13.911
I was bored. Needed a change.

12:19.852 --> 12:21.686
Ha... is everything OK?

12:21.721 --> 12:23.721
Yeah. I've been worried sick.

12:23.756 --> 12:26.457
With all these attacks,
you shouldn't be out on your own.

12:26.492 --> 12:28.693
Well, I'm not on my own.
I'm here with you,

12:28.728 --> 12:30.828
High Warlock of Brooklyn.

12:33.833 --> 12:37.401
A body was found
in Williamsburg.

12:37.437 --> 12:38.769
Have you heard anything?

12:38.805 --> 12:40.871
No...

12:40.907 --> 12:43.641
but warlocks don't report
their misdeeds to me.

12:43.676 --> 12:46.477
If they did,
my phone would never stop ringing.

12:51.484 --> 12:52.616
Magnus, I need your hair.

12:52.652 --> 12:54.518
It's just a strand

12:54.554 --> 12:56.554
for a DNA test to clear you.

12:56.589 --> 12:57.766
I didn't realize
there was anything

12:57.790 --> 12:59.423
I needed to be cleared of.

12:59.892 --> 13:01.592
Do you not trust my word?

13:01.627 --> 13:02.560
Of course I trust you.

13:02.595 --> 13:03.839
I know you had nothing
to do with this.

13:03.863 --> 13:06.697
It's just, this is...
it's Clave orders.

13:07.934 --> 13:09.633
I see.

13:09.669 --> 13:11.836
So again you're just
blindly carrying out orders?

13:11.871 --> 13:13.904
What happened to
following your gut?

13:13.940 --> 13:16.674
Magnus. Shadowhunters
are being slaughtered.

13:17.814 --> 13:21.512
I'm just asking for a strand of hair.
Let's not be overdramatic.

13:21.547 --> 13:22.813
Well...

13:23.916 --> 13:25.683
I wouldn't want to
be overdramatic.

13:38.598 --> 13:39.430
Thank you.

13:39.465 --> 13:40.765
Get out.

13:40.878 --> 13:41.799
What?

13:41.834 --> 13:43.434
Magnus, come on...

13:43.469 --> 13:45.469
(RUSHING AIR)

13:54.781 --> 13:56.413
(SHARPLY INHALING)

13:59.452 --> 14:00.518
Luke did it.

14:00.553 --> 14:02.486
He gave a DNA sample.

14:02.522 --> 14:03.854
It was his idea.

14:03.890 --> 14:05.523
He knew it would clear him.

14:05.558 --> 14:06.657
You know my Bubbie Helen?

14:06.692 --> 14:07.892
Yeah, of course.

14:07.927 --> 14:09.627
When she was little,

14:09.662 --> 14:12.630
her family owned a
bakery in Poland.

14:12.665 --> 14:15.432
One day, these soldiers came in

14:15.468 --> 14:16.712
and asked to put a
star in the window.

14:16.736 --> 14:18.669
They wanted to know which
shops were Jewish-run.

14:18.704 --> 14:20.471
You know, no big deal.
For their records.

14:21.641 --> 14:22.918
Then they had to
wear white armbands.

14:22.942 --> 14:24.842
And they couldn't
ride the train.

14:24.877 --> 14:26.744
Then they were forced
to ride the train.

14:26.779 --> 14:29.747
My Bubbie Helen was the only
one in her family to survive.

14:31.906 --> 14:34.451
Simon...

14:35.688 --> 14:37.688
I am so sorry.
I didn't realize...

14:37.723 --> 14:39.623
That's why I can't do
what you're asking.

14:40.760 --> 14:41.760
For her.

14:49.502 --> 14:51.735
(PHONE RINGING)

14:51.771 --> 14:53.404
(BEEPING)

14:53.439 --> 14:54.439
Hi Simon.

14:54.473 --> 14:54.905
Where are you?

14:54.941 --> 14:56.407
<i>Two blocks away</i>

14:56.442 --> 14:57.553
from where I was when you
called me 20 seconds ago.

14:57.577 --> 14:58.542
You see, this is stupid.

14:58.578 --> 14:59.655
I should have never
let you convince me

14:59.679 --> 15:00.722
<i>that you were OK
to walk home alone!</i>

15:00.746 --> 15:02.680
I'm fine!
I'll be home in like...

15:02.715 --> 15:03.614
(GASPING)

15:03.649 --> 15:04.715
(GROANING)

15:04.750 --> 15:05.883
Clary?

15:05.918 --> 15:07.484
- (GASPING)
- <i>Hello?</i>

15:07.520 --> 15:08.552
<i>Hello?</i>

15:08.588 --> 15:09.720
(GROANING)

15:09.755 --> 15:11.555
Clary! Clary, you OK?!

15:12.658 --> 15:13.658
(METAL SCRAPING)

15:17.797 --> 15:20.531
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

15:20.566 --> 15:21.566
(HEAVY EXHALING)

15:25.465 --> 15:29.683
(RAPID FOOTFALLS)

15:30.639 --> 15:31.618
SIMON: Clary!

15:31.653 --> 15:32.919
Clary! You OK?

15:33.227 --> 15:35.361
Hey! Can you hear me?

15:35.367 --> 15:36.867
Clary?!

15:38.059 --> 15:40.226
IZZY: You'll have four
training sessions a day...

15:40.261 --> 15:42.294
demon strategy, weapons,
combat, and endurance.

15:42.330 --> 15:43.901
Breakfast starts at five.

15:43.938 --> 15:46.806
If you are late,
all you'll have is a cold bran muffin.

15:46.899 --> 15:48.334
I don't need breakfast.

15:48.369 --> 15:50.236
When do we start training?

15:50.304 --> 15:51.370
Now?

15:51.406 --> 15:52.632
First thing tomorrow.

15:52.661 --> 15:53.741
Right now I have a mission.

15:54.175 --> 15:55.665
Great, let's go.

15:55.671 --> 15:56.928
Whoa, slow down! OK?

15:56.964 --> 15:58.527
You don't get to
go out in the field

15:58.613 --> 15:59.758
until you complete
your training.

15:59.782 --> 16:01.782
But I have more medals
than anyone in my class.

16:01.817 --> 16:03.717
I did so well in the simulator,

16:03.752 --> 16:05.485
they had to write
a new code for it.

16:05.521 --> 16:07.621
IZZY SIGHING: That's
because you hacked it.

16:12.412 --> 16:15.346
This is real, Max. Dangerous.

16:15.381 --> 16:16.481
I can handle it.

16:16.516 --> 16:17.448
Please?

16:17.484 --> 16:19.350
I'll follow orders.

16:21.554 --> 16:23.321
Patience, young Shadowhunter.

16:23.356 --> 16:25.256
You'll be out there soon enough.

16:25.291 --> 16:26.557
(SIGHING)

16:31.598 --> 16:32.630
(SOUL MUSIC)

16:32.665 --> 16:34.298
<i>♪ Send me a daydream ♪</i>

16:34.334 --> 16:35.533
(KNOCKING)

16:35.568 --> 16:38.302
(RUSHING AIR)

16:38.338 --> 16:39.637
<i>♪</i>

16:39.672 --> 16:41.205
How'd you know it was me?

16:41.241 --> 16:44.242
My powers are wild and
beyond understanding.

16:44.277 --> 16:46.577
And I saw you crossing
the street outside.

16:46.613 --> 16:48.379
So, have you come to talk me

16:48.414 --> 16:50.314
into spitting into
a cup for the Clave?

16:50.350 --> 16:51.315
You kidding me?

16:51.351 --> 16:53.384
Look, I'm all for
stopping those murders,

16:53.419 --> 16:55.686
but when the DNA brigade came
knocking, I portalled out.

16:55.722 --> 16:58.289
I had that shop in Salem...

16:58.324 --> 16:59.690
this isn't my first witch hunt.

17:00.593 --> 17:01.593
I'll drink to that.

17:02.662 --> 17:04.529
Oops. I suppose I already am.

17:04.564 --> 17:06.230
(CHUCKLING)

17:06.266 --> 17:07.330
So...

17:07.367 --> 17:08.465
came by to bring you these.

17:08.501 --> 17:12.236
<i>♪ But I had to be a big girl ♪</i>

17:12.271 --> 17:13.271
<i>♪ And get out on my own ♪</i>

17:13.306 --> 17:14.338
Dragonfly wings?

17:14.374 --> 17:15.439
I thought it might help.

17:15.474 --> 17:17.441
From when you lost your powers.

17:17.477 --> 17:19.644
After being blasted by
that greater demon...

17:19.679 --> 17:22.246
<i>♪</i>

17:22.281 --> 17:23.381
A disturbing ordeal.

17:23.415 --> 17:26.284
<i>♪ This isn't easy... ♪</i>

17:26.319 --> 17:27.518
Whiskey rocks.

17:27.554 --> 17:28.686
Your heartache drink.

17:28.721 --> 17:30.421
<i>♪ This isn't what I dreamed... ♪</i>

17:30.456 --> 17:31.355
Not always.

17:31.391 --> 17:32.590
It's me, Mag.

17:32.625 --> 17:34.492
I've known you for centuries.

17:34.527 --> 17:35.693
Pour me one.

17:35.728 --> 17:37.540
<i>♪ You broke my heart and
you let us fall astray ♪</i>

17:37.564 --> 17:39.230
Talk.

17:39.265 --> 17:40.431
<i>♪</i>

17:40.466 --> 17:43.467
Or not. Either way,
you should never drink alone.

17:43.503 --> 17:46.637
<i>♪ Break away... ♪</i>

17:46.673 --> 17:48.372
So you didn't see
the attacker at all?

17:48.408 --> 17:49.408
No description? Nothing?

17:49.442 --> 17:50.619
It was hard to see
and I had to choose.

17:50.643 --> 17:52.243
Either go after
them or help Clary.

17:52.278 --> 17:53.678
Would you have done
it differently?

17:55.315 --> 17:56.315
You better get going.

17:56.349 --> 17:57.349
No.

17:57.383 --> 17:58.561
I'm not going anywhere
until she wakes up.

17:58.585 --> 17:59.585
Under the circumstances,

17:59.619 --> 18:01.452
there's a lockout order
on all Downworlders.

18:01.487 --> 18:03.254
What else is new.
Jace, I saved her.

18:03.289 --> 18:04.355
I brought her here,

18:04.390 --> 18:06.235
and when she wakes up I'm
gonna be there for her.

18:06.259 --> 18:07.592
I wish that were possible,

18:07.652 --> 18:09.318
but the Institute
is on high alert.

18:09.329 --> 18:10.057
There are new rules here...

18:10.089 --> 18:11.054
I don't care about your rules.

18:11.090 --> 18:12.664
I care about Clary.
I'm not leaving.

18:12.684 --> 18:14.254
It's not a request, Mr. Lewis.

18:14.434 --> 18:15.399
Look, I'm...

18:15.435 --> 18:16.645
I'm not a criminal,
I'm her boyfriend...

18:16.669 --> 18:17.702
Simon.

18:18.671 --> 18:20.271
Please don't make this worse.

18:20.306 --> 18:22.473
I'll let you know as soon as
I hear anything about her.

18:24.738 --> 18:26.410
You will leave this Institute

18:26.446 --> 18:27.886
or I'll have you
escorted to a cell.

18:28.748 --> 18:30.448
I will not ask again.

18:30.483 --> 18:31.616
You don't have to.

18:31.651 --> 18:33.351
I'm not leaving.

18:39.259 --> 18:40.458
Jace! Tell Clary I'm here!

18:40.493 --> 18:42.360
Tell Clary I'm here!

18:42.395 --> 18:44.562
Simon has been
helpful in the past.

18:44.597 --> 18:46.197
He's an ally.

18:46.232 --> 18:48.444
Don't you think throwing him
in jail is a little excessive?

18:48.468 --> 18:51.369
A Downworlder cannot
challenge our authority.

18:51.404 --> 18:53.204
Not in times like these.

18:53.239 --> 18:55.206
(RINGING)

18:56.342 --> 18:58.442
(BEEPING)

18:58.478 --> 19:00.211
Another body.

19:00.413 --> 19:02.246
(WHEELS SQUEAKING)

19:06.319 --> 19:07.551
ALEC: It's Hillwater.

19:07.587 --> 19:09.520
Looks like a vampire attack.

19:11.324 --> 19:12.324
We need a new plan.

19:12.358 --> 19:15.493
These are from the R
and D Team in Alicante.

19:15.528 --> 19:16.627
We've always been able

19:16.663 --> 19:18.629
to track Shadowhunters
through their runes.

19:18.665 --> 19:21.399
Now we can track Downworlders
through GPS chips.

19:21.434 --> 19:23.234
What are you saying?

19:23.269 --> 19:24.580
That we round up
the Downworlders

19:24.604 --> 19:26.237
and involuntarily chip them?

19:26.272 --> 19:29.707
Mr. Lightwood,
perhaps your personal relationships

19:29.742 --> 19:31.475
are clouding your objectivity.

19:31.511 --> 19:33.591
My personal relationships
have nothing to do with it.

19:34.681 --> 19:36.447
No, you know what?

19:36.482 --> 19:37.660
Maybe they have
everything to do with it,

19:37.684 --> 19:40.518
because it was a warlock who
told me to always follow my gut,

19:40.553 --> 19:41.697
and that is just plain wrong.

19:41.721 --> 19:44.488
No. Downworlders preying
on Shadowhunters,

19:44.524 --> 19:45.489
that is what's wrong.

19:45.525 --> 19:46.691
You sound like Valentine.

19:46.726 --> 19:50.528
Valentine wants those people dead.
I'm trying to help them.

19:50.563 --> 19:52.296
Those people?

19:53.733 --> 19:54.733
Jace, you can't do this.

19:57.537 --> 19:59.637
Alec, look at this.

19:59.672 --> 20:02.273
Too many Shadowhunters
are dying.

20:12.385 --> 20:14.618
(GLASSES CLINKING)

20:14.654 --> 20:16.687
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATION)

20:16.723 --> 20:19.357
(INSTRUMENTAL INDIE ROCK MUSIC)

20:19.392 --> 20:20.591
MAIA: I'm sorry, gentlemen!

20:20.626 --> 20:21.626
This isn't a leather bar.

20:21.661 --> 20:24.395
Hm. I'm here on Clave business.

20:24.430 --> 20:26.530
Clave business? Do I curtsy?

20:26.566 --> 20:28.644
If you really want to.
Are there any mundanes in here?

20:28.668 --> 20:30.401
No.

20:30.436 --> 20:32.536
There's a new mandate,

20:32.572 --> 20:34.438
for everyone's safety:

20:34.474 --> 20:35.740
GPS implants.

20:41.581 --> 20:43.247
You've got to be kidding me.

20:43.282 --> 20:45.383
The Clave has always been
able to track Shadowhunters

20:45.418 --> 20:46.462
through their runes.
This is no different.

20:46.486 --> 20:47.685
This is very different.

20:47.720 --> 20:50.254
Hey everybody!

20:50.289 --> 20:53.557
The Clave wants to
implant tracking chips

20:53.593 --> 20:57.261
in all of us.
Like pets. Who's in?

20:57.296 --> 20:58.329
It isn't like that.

20:58.364 --> 21:00.431
This is just temporary,
until we catch the killer.

21:00.466 --> 21:02.366
(METALLIC RINGING)

21:02.402 --> 21:03.734
JACE SIGHING: Again?

21:03.770 --> 21:05.547
I thought you would have
learned the first time.

21:05.571 --> 21:08.272
But apparently,
Shadowhunters aren't the brightest bulbs.

21:08.307 --> 21:11.475
Alright, hey. Look,
we can get this done without any violence.

21:11.511 --> 21:13.477
Where's the fun in that?

21:13.513 --> 21:15.446
(GRUNTING)

21:15.481 --> 21:16.714
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

21:16.749 --> 21:18.382
(THUDDING)

21:18.418 --> 21:19.418
No!

21:24.050 --> 21:29.086
(MUTED AMBIENT NOISES)

21:29.136 --> 21:30.579
(GRUNTING)

21:30.646 --> 21:31.683
(GLASS SHATTERING)

21:31.782 --> 21:32.811
(GRUNTING)

21:32.838 --> 21:34.098
(GRUNTING)

21:34.171 --> 21:35.818
(GRUNTING)

21:35.931 --> 21:37.671
(BOTH GRUNTING)

21:37.832 --> 21:39.632
Maia! Maia, stop!

21:39.668 --> 21:40.911
The Clave's gone too
far, Lucian.

21:40.935 --> 21:41.868
Let them fight.

21:41.903 --> 21:42.935
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

21:42.971 --> 21:44.637
(BOTH GRUNTING)

21:44.673 --> 21:45.471
Wait!

21:45.507 --> 21:46.839
(ELECTRONIC HISSING)

21:46.875 --> 21:47.875
(GROANING)

21:49.678 --> 21:50.543
You son of a bitch.

21:50.578 --> 21:51.667
(GROANING)

21:51.746 --> 21:52.906
LUCIAN SHOUTING: I said stop!

21:57.291 --> 21:58.411
You want a Downworld revolt?

21:59.200 --> 22:00.200
This is how it starts.

22:00.689 --> 22:02.655
They came after Clary.

22:02.691 --> 22:03.623
What?

22:03.658 --> 22:05.958
Look, she's OK, Luke, but...

22:05.994 --> 22:08.203
It's not about Clary.

22:08.237 --> 22:10.036
And it's not about those
dead Shadowhunters.

22:10.532 --> 22:12.765
It's about starting a war.

22:12.801 --> 22:15.568
Do you want that
blood on your hands?

22:19.841 --> 22:20.873
Get out of here.

22:28.817 --> 22:36.817
(CLARY SIGHING)

22:42.831 --> 22:43.930
What happened?

22:43.965 --> 22:45.798
You were drugged.

22:45.834 --> 22:48.501
Fortunately, Simon got to
you before it was too late.

22:48.536 --> 22:50.470
They tried to kill me?

22:53.742 --> 22:55.056
- Where's Simon?
- Hey.

22:55.109 --> 22:56.109
Take it easy.

22:56.544 --> 22:59.645
Where is he? Is he OK?

22:59.681 --> 23:02.582
He refused to
leave the premises.

23:02.617 --> 23:03.961
Inquisitor Herondale
had him taken down

23:03.985 --> 23:05.551
to the detention level.

23:05.587 --> 23:08.554
She locked up Simon?

23:14.016 --> 23:15.200
You cannot be down here.

23:15.330 --> 23:17.263
- I have clearance.
- Not anymore.

23:17.292 --> 23:18.424
Inquisitor's orders.

23:18.493 --> 23:20.226
Duncan, please.
I need to see Simon.

23:22.804 --> 23:23.936
Simon!

23:23.972 --> 23:24.871
Clary?

23:24.906 --> 23:26.839
- Simon!
- SIMON KNOCKING: Clary!

23:26.875 --> 23:29.609
Simon, if you can hear me,
I will get you out of here!

23:29.644 --> 23:30.877
Simon!

23:31.813 --> 23:33.713
DOT: Alec Lightwood...

23:33.748 --> 23:34.981
No wonder you're a mess.

23:35.016 --> 23:37.583
Mortals are always
trouble, you know that.

23:37.619 --> 23:39.530
Says the warlock who had
a fling with Mark Twain.

23:39.554 --> 23:40.753
What can I say?

23:40.789 --> 23:44.624
- I'm a sucker for a man with a moustache.
- Me too,

23:44.659 --> 23:46.459
but only if it belongs
to Freddie Mercury.

23:46.494 --> 23:47.627
(GASPING)

23:47.662 --> 23:50.630
So that's why you dragged me
to all those Queen concerts!

23:50.665 --> 23:53.772
DOT LAUGHING: We
Will Rock You indeed.

23:53.778 --> 23:56.045
Oh, don't be crude.
I fall in love with the soul

23:56.838 --> 23:58.471
before the sex.

23:58.540 --> 24:00.840
Was it my soul you
fell in love with?

24:00.875 --> 24:03.776
What we had was wonderful.

24:03.812 --> 24:07.547
That was... wow!

24:07.588 --> 24:09.819
- That was almost a century ago.
- (SIGHING)

24:09.905 --> 24:11.237
But that's not what I mean.

24:11.920 --> 24:14.720
So find a warlock soul
to fall in love with.

24:14.756 --> 24:17.723
Then when the Clave declares
war on the Downworld,

24:17.759 --> 24:20.560
your boyfriend's not trying to
hit you up for a cheek swab.

24:20.595 --> 24:21.627
OK.

24:21.663 --> 24:24.897
- So, if warlocks are so divine...
- Mhm...

24:24.933 --> 24:28.501
why haven't you hooked up
with any handsome magic-maker

24:28.536 --> 24:29.702
in the past six decades?

24:29.737 --> 24:31.971
Not that anyone's counting.

24:32.006 --> 24:33.973
Touché.

24:34.008 --> 24:37.510
What can I say?
It's hard to find a warlock

24:37.545 --> 24:39.612
who's super hot and
lives in this realm.

24:40.949 --> 24:43.683
And who's also a good dancer.

24:43.718 --> 24:46.619
Why, Miss Dorothea...

24:46.654 --> 24:47.720
Is that a challenge?

24:51.593 --> 24:53.526
OK. I'm on my way.

24:53.561 --> 24:54.561
(ELEVATOR BEEPING)

24:54.596 --> 24:55.862
So Imogen says

24:55.897 --> 24:58.158
to lock up Simon and
you just let it happen?

24:58.227 --> 24:59.811
Clary, I tried to help Simon.

24:59.934 --> 25:01.479
You know I wouldn't
have done any of this

25:01.503 --> 25:02.646
if he hadn't broken Clave rules.

25:02.670 --> 25:03.910
Oh, suddenly you're into rules?

25:03.938 --> 25:05.771
You know,
Jace Herondale might have

25:05.807 --> 25:07.740
some kind of family
name to live up to,

25:07.775 --> 25:09.775
but the Jace I know
would break any rule

25:09.811 --> 25:11.511
for the people he cares about.

25:11.546 --> 25:12.745
People are dying.

25:12.814 --> 25:15.581
People I've known my entire life.
People I trained with.

25:15.617 --> 25:17.717
There are no easy
choices right now.

25:17.752 --> 25:19.652
A team just found
Lockheart dead.

25:19.687 --> 25:21.521
And we've just
caught his killer.

25:21.990 --> 25:23.556
Maia, what's going on?

25:23.591 --> 25:25.775
HERONDALE: Lockheart was mauled by a wolf.
Ms. Roberts

25:25.834 --> 25:28.825
was found a block away,
minutes after the kill.

25:28.930 --> 25:31.831
I was walking home from work.
What, is that a crime now too?

25:31.866 --> 25:33.666
Did anyone see you
walking home from work?

25:33.701 --> 25:35.935
It's New York City.
A lot of people were a block away.

25:35.970 --> 25:37.737
An hour ago, this wolf

25:37.772 --> 25:40.282
viciously attacked Jace for
carrying out a Clave mandate.

25:40.315 --> 25:42.208
To put a tracking
chip in my neck!

25:42.250 --> 25:43.250
Wait... what?!

25:43.305 --> 25:45.138
You know,
I have been stopped by cops

25:45.513 --> 25:46.824
for no other reason
than being black,

25:46.848 --> 25:49.749
but I thought the Shadowhunters
were more evolved than that.

25:49.784 --> 25:52.518
Jace, I didn't do this.

25:54.789 --> 25:56.589
Six Shadowhunters are dead.

25:56.624 --> 25:58.758
Don't let your emotions
cloud your judgment.

25:58.793 --> 26:00.726
Isn't fear an emotion?

26:00.762 --> 26:01.928
Because that's all this is.

26:01.963 --> 26:04.630
Tracking people because of
the kind of blood they have.

26:04.666 --> 26:06.262
Locking them up
without recourse?

26:06.396 --> 26:08.430
Is that what the
Clave stands for?

26:08.465 --> 26:10.465
Your idealism is charming,

26:10.500 --> 26:12.700
but when they wheel in
the next dead Shadowhunter

26:12.769 --> 26:15.770
with their runes carved out,
what will you tell their family?

26:15.806 --> 26:18.540
What will your ideals
have done for any of them?

26:19.609 --> 26:21.376
Put her downstairs
with the vampire.

26:22.679 --> 26:23.611
(RINGING)

26:23.647 --> 26:24.779
HERONDALE: Excuse me.

26:24.815 --> 26:26.681
Jace, tell her to stop.

26:26.716 --> 26:28.616
You know this is wrong.

26:30.754 --> 26:32.454
I'm needed in Idris.

26:32.489 --> 26:34.689
The Institute is in your hands
now, Jace.

26:34.724 --> 26:37.392
Make me proud.

26:40.730 --> 26:42.297
Clary...

26:42.332 --> 26:45.700
there's no perfect way to do this.
I'm doing my best.

26:45.735 --> 26:47.702
You know, not too long ago,

26:47.737 --> 26:49.671
everyone thought
you had demon blood.

26:50.874 --> 26:53.608
If you weren't a Herondale,
she'd be locking you up, too.

26:57.681 --> 26:59.647
(SIGHING)

27:01.384 --> 27:02.617
(HORNS HONKING)

27:04.387 --> 27:05.620
(GATE CREAKING OPEN)

27:05.655 --> 27:11.326
(TWO SETS OF FOOTSTEPS)

27:11.361 --> 27:12.760
You shouldn't be out alone.

27:12.796 --> 27:14.796
Raphael...

27:14.831 --> 27:16.598
thank you for coming.

27:16.633 --> 27:19.434
Just so you know,
Simon and I would have never have done

27:19.469 --> 27:21.481
- anything to hurt your sister...
- I didn't come here for apologies.

27:21.505 --> 27:22.704
I came to reason with you.

27:22.739 --> 27:24.339
For my clan.

27:24.374 --> 27:25.340
They're not going to sit around

27:25.375 --> 27:26.519
and let the Clave
put trackers in them.

27:26.543 --> 27:27.575
I don't want that either.

27:27.611 --> 27:28.776
I want to stop all of this.

27:28.812 --> 27:31.513
So if there's anything you
know about these murders...

27:31.548 --> 27:32.758
I can tell you
it's not a vampire.

27:32.782 --> 27:35.617
We would never remove
runes from a Shadowhunter.

27:35.652 --> 27:36.652
Why is that?

27:38.555 --> 27:40.655
From the time
before the Accords,

27:40.690 --> 27:44.592
the Downworlders were hunted
by Shadowhunters for sport.

27:44.628 --> 27:48.630
They took our fangs, werewolf
claws, and warlock marks

27:48.665 --> 27:51.366
as trophies. The vampires swore

27:51.401 --> 27:53.701
we would never let that happen again.
To anyone.

27:53.737 --> 27:56.638
That's horrible...

27:56.673 --> 27:59.741
but if no vampires are
involved, what about Keytower?

27:59.776 --> 28:01.476
His blood was drained.

28:01.511 --> 28:04.479
RAPHAEL: My guess? A diversion.

28:04.514 --> 28:05.691
Throw the investigation
off track.

28:05.715 --> 28:08.516
What else do you know?

28:13.423 --> 28:15.690
Raphael. I respect your
loyalty to the Downworld.

28:15.725 --> 28:16.591
But please...

28:16.626 --> 28:19.360
We're desperate.

28:19.396 --> 28:21.529
Innocent people are dying.

28:23.700 --> 28:26.401
Back in the 80's,
the Downworld came together

28:26.436 --> 28:28.469
to make some demands the
Clave wouldn't agree to.

28:28.505 --> 28:30.405
And it got pretty ugly.

28:30.440 --> 28:32.440
I overheard a Seelie
Knight tell Camille

28:32.475 --> 28:34.420
that the only way to gain
the Shadowhunters' respect

28:34.444 --> 28:36.578
was to show them how
dangerous we are.

28:36.613 --> 28:38.613
Beyond killing them,

28:38.648 --> 28:43.451
he suggested an extra step...
taking their runes.

28:43.486 --> 28:45.720
Which Seelie?

28:55.629 --> 28:57.782
<i>♪ Maybelline New York ♪</i>

28:57.902 --> 29:02.305
(VICTROLA MUSIC)

29:02.368 --> 29:04.401
<i>♪</i>

29:04.435 --> 29:05.948
(CHUCKLING)

29:06.010 --> 29:10.329
<i>♪</i>

29:25.916 --> 29:28.083
My life would be a boring
tragedy without you.

29:28.118 --> 29:30.252
It would indeed.

29:38.539 --> 29:39.672
I'm sorry...

29:39.714 --> 29:41.647
Don't be.

29:41.683 --> 29:43.449
I'm in love with Alec.

29:43.484 --> 29:44.484
I know.

29:44.519 --> 29:46.419
I just...

29:46.454 --> 29:47.687
Had a moment.

29:47.722 --> 29:49.555
MAGNUS: And a bottle of whiskey.

29:49.591 --> 29:52.658
You are incredibly
beautiful, Dot.

29:52.694 --> 29:57.630
And soulful. Generous.

29:57.665 --> 29:59.732
But... I'm afraid

29:59.767 --> 30:03.736
I've always been a
one-soul-at-a-time kind of guy.

30:03.771 --> 30:07.506
Alec's lucky to have you.

30:15.943 --> 30:17.416
MAIA: Why didn't you just leave?

30:17.452 --> 30:19.385
There was nothing
you could do for her.

30:19.420 --> 30:21.320
SIMON: I just...

30:21.356 --> 30:22.421
couldn't.

30:22.457 --> 30:25.458
And I kind of thought Jace
would stand up for me.

30:25.493 --> 30:27.360
Yeah, Jace looks lost.

30:27.395 --> 30:30.329
Like a deer caught
in headlights.

30:30.365 --> 30:31.664
I guess I get it.

30:31.699 --> 30:32.665
Get what?

30:32.700 --> 30:34.667
That he's under the
Inquisitor's spell?

30:34.702 --> 30:36.535
I know what it's like,

30:36.571 --> 30:39.338
to want so badly to
have real family.

30:39.374 --> 30:41.407
The things you'll do...

30:41.442 --> 30:43.476
Even for the world's
most terrifying grandma?

30:43.511 --> 30:45.411
Totally...

30:45.446 --> 30:46.590
I mean,
you should have seen her face

30:46.614 --> 30:48.314
when Clary went off on her.

30:48.349 --> 30:49.682
That woman was legit scared.

30:49.717 --> 30:51.484
Clary was on fire.

30:51.519 --> 30:54.253
If I didn't know any better...

30:54.288 --> 30:55.421
I'd say you like Clary now.

30:55.456 --> 30:57.456
She's growing on me.

30:59.527 --> 31:01.694
Don't screw it up, Simon.

31:01.729 --> 31:03.729
I don't plan to...

31:06.300 --> 31:07.444
if I ever get out of here.

31:07.468 --> 31:10.269
You're a Daylighter now.

31:10.304 --> 31:12.738
Does... that come with
any other new tricks

31:12.774 --> 31:14.440
that could break us out of here?

31:15.710 --> 31:16.609
No.

31:16.644 --> 31:18.444
But I've realized

31:18.479 --> 31:21.514
that being a Daylighter is
like, totally overrated.

31:21.549 --> 31:23.449
Like, I should have
got something cool,

31:23.484 --> 31:25.462
- heat vision, or invisibility...
- (DOOR CREAKING OPEN)

31:25.486 --> 31:26.664
- If only you were invisible.
- Clary!

31:26.688 --> 31:27.688
Clary!

31:29.590 --> 31:31.691
You OK? I tried to stay
but they wouldn't let me...

31:31.726 --> 31:32.692
CLARY: No, it's alright.
It's OK.

31:32.727 --> 31:35.461
You know damn well I
didn't kill anyone.

31:35.496 --> 31:36.496
Yeah, well, even so,

31:36.531 --> 31:38.330
I should probably let
you cool out down here

31:38.366 --> 31:39.476
for that right hook you landed.

31:39.500 --> 31:41.300
You deserved it.

31:43.538 --> 31:45.271
Yeah, I did.

31:45.306 --> 31:47.273
I was wrong.

31:47.308 --> 31:49.341
I'm sorry.

31:49.377 --> 31:52.278
An apology... from you.

31:53.448 --> 31:55.715
Wow. There's a first
time for everything.

31:59.754 --> 32:01.420
(FOOTSTEPS)

32:01.456 --> 32:04.256
So you wore his shirt home,
and you kept it for how long?

32:04.292 --> 32:05.335
You should be glad I kept it.

32:05.359 --> 32:06.959
It's the only thing
helping us track him.

32:08.362 --> 32:10.274
I can't believe Meliorn
would do something like this.

32:10.298 --> 32:12.018
RAPHAEL: The Fair Folk
work in strange ways.

32:14.435 --> 32:15.501
We've got company.

32:26.481 --> 32:28.447
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

32:28.483 --> 32:29.483
Wait!

32:31.486 --> 32:34.386
By the Angel, Max!
What are you doing here?

32:34.422 --> 32:36.422
I tracked you here.

32:36.457 --> 32:38.290
Told you I was the
best in my class.

32:38.326 --> 32:40.392
IZZY: You could have
gotten yourself killed.

32:40.428 --> 32:41.594
I smell Shadowhunter blood.

32:44.665 --> 32:46.532
Wanna prove you're the
best in your class?

32:46.601 --> 32:49.268
Stay here and stay hidden.

32:49.303 --> 32:50.569
Do you understand?

32:55.276 --> 32:57.276
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

32:57.311 --> 32:58.577
<i>♪</i>

33:10.391 --> 33:11.490
This is not my doing.

33:11.526 --> 33:12.625
I was tracking the killer,

33:12.660 --> 33:14.360
but I'm afraid I
arrived too late.

33:14.395 --> 33:16.462
Don't believe anything he says.

33:16.497 --> 33:17.663
Seelies can't lie.

33:17.698 --> 33:20.266
Yeah, but they'll spin the
truth until you're dizzy.

33:21.636 --> 33:23.369
I can help you find the killer.

33:24.672 --> 33:26.605
It's a Seelie,
I can tell you that.

33:26.641 --> 33:28.340
And I can track them.

33:28.376 --> 33:30.276
Let's go.

33:30.311 --> 33:31.471
Isabelle, it could be a trap.

33:34.382 --> 33:36.315
I believe him, OK?

33:36.350 --> 33:38.384
I need you to take Max
back to the Institute

33:38.419 --> 33:42.521
where he'll be safe.

33:42.557 --> 33:45.524
<i>♪</i>

33:47.261 --> 33:48.261
IZZY: Max!

33:51.365 --> 33:52.398
Oh, no...

33:55.603 --> 33:57.303
Max!

33:58.439 --> 33:59.672
IZZY SCREAMING: Max!

34:00.308 --> 34:03.509
(HIGH-PITCHED NOISES)

34:06.681 --> 34:09.248
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

34:10.685 --> 34:12.585
(FLUORESCENT LIGHT BUZZING)

34:22.362 --> 34:23.661
Awake already?

34:23.697 --> 34:26.565
Come near me and I'll kill you.

34:26.601 --> 34:28.367
(LAUGHING)

34:28.402 --> 34:30.636
KAELIE: You don't deserve this.

34:30.670 --> 34:34.473
But Shadowhunters need
to feel what it's like

34:34.507 --> 34:36.542
to lose the ones that they love.

34:36.577 --> 34:39.612
My brother Samuel was all
I had in this world...

34:39.647 --> 34:41.547
and now he's gone!

34:43.317 --> 34:45.284
Thanks to your brother, Jace.

34:45.652 --> 34:47.253
(GASPING)

34:48.422 --> 34:49.422
(GRUNTING)

34:49.623 --> 34:51.623
One more move and you're dead.

34:54.495 --> 34:55.495
(GRUNTING)

34:57.598 --> 34:58.678
MELIORN: It's over, Kaelie!

35:01.335 --> 35:03.335
The Shadowhunters led
us into a massacre.

35:03.371 --> 35:05.304
Why are you on their side?

35:05.339 --> 35:07.306
- It is not a matter of
sides, Kaelie, - (HISSING)

35:07.341 --> 35:08.274
it is a matter of what is right.

35:08.309 --> 35:09.241
(GRUNTING)

35:09.277 --> 35:10.442
(BLADE SWISHING)

35:11.345 --> 35:12.345
(GRUNTING)

35:13.447 --> 35:14.513
MAX: I'm sorry.

35:14.548 --> 35:15.548
(BOTH GRUNTING)

35:16.450 --> 35:18.350
(GRUNTING)

35:19.420 --> 35:20.420
- (SIZZLING)
- (GROANING)

35:20.688 --> 35:22.388
(METALLIC SCRAPING)

35:23.291 --> 35:24.390
(METALLIC SCRAPING)

35:26.394 --> 35:27.660
(GASPING)

35:33.701 --> 35:35.701
(METALLIC CLANGING)

35:52.653 --> 35:56.291
IZZY: She had everything: Werewolf
claws, vampire fangs,

35:56.379 --> 35:59.179
Seelie blades.
She used it to make it

35:59.215 --> 36:00.425
look like a Downworld uprising.

36:00.449 --> 36:01.515
The question is, why?

36:01.550 --> 36:03.450
We're not sure.

36:03.486 --> 36:05.419
But it has to go beyond
covering her tracks.

36:05.454 --> 36:07.221
I agree.

36:07.256 --> 36:08.522
That's great work, Iz.

36:09.558 --> 36:11.258
I hear Max is back
up on his feet

36:11.294 --> 36:12.614
and ready to take
over the world.

36:14.025 --> 36:16.263
How are you doing? Are you OK?

36:16.299 --> 36:18.365
Getting better
one day at a time.

36:18.401 --> 36:19.600
Good.

36:19.635 --> 36:21.368
JACE: We'll keep
investigating Kaelie.

36:21.404 --> 36:23.404
But in the meantime,

36:23.439 --> 36:26.206
my first official act as Head
of the Institute is going

36:26.242 --> 36:27.408
to be somewhat controversial,

36:27.443 --> 36:29.343
so I'm gonna need your help.

36:30.513 --> 36:32.313
You're taking over.

36:32.348 --> 36:34.315
The Seelie investigation?

36:34.350 --> 36:35.683
No.

36:36.519 --> 36:38.519
I mean you, Alec Lightwood,

36:38.554 --> 36:40.521
are now the Head of
the New York Institute.

36:45.628 --> 36:46.628
Can you do that?

36:46.662 --> 36:48.295
Yeah.

36:48.331 --> 36:49.430
I mean, like you said,

36:49.465 --> 36:52.199
being a Herondale comes
with certain perks.

36:52.234 --> 36:53.594
Naming a successor
is one of them.

36:56.205 --> 36:57.271
You were right.

36:57.306 --> 36:59.206
Downworlders and Shadowhunters,

36:59.241 --> 37:02.343
We're all a mix of
human, angel and demon.

37:02.378 --> 37:04.411
If we let the Clave
forget that...

37:06.482 --> 37:07.614
we deserve a revolt.

37:10.386 --> 37:11.552
I'll always be a soldier.

37:12.621 --> 37:13.661
But you're a leader, Alec.

37:17.526 --> 37:18.686
I have your first assignment.

37:20.463 --> 37:21.463
Bring it.

37:23.399 --> 37:24.543
SIMON: This is gonna
be humiliating.

37:24.567 --> 37:26.407
What if there's only
like, two or three people?

37:26.435 --> 37:27.446
And I'm not even
ready to perform

37:27.470 --> 37:28.435
in front of two or
three people yet.

37:28.471 --> 37:30.304
Unless they're really drunk.

37:30.339 --> 37:31.579
Simon. Have I ever lied to you?

37:31.607 --> 37:33.407
Not that I know of.

37:33.442 --> 37:36.276
Then believe me
when I tell you...

37:36.312 --> 37:38.412
you are going to crush it.

37:38.447 --> 37:40.381
- (SIGHING)
- OK?

37:40.416 --> 37:41.348
OK.

37:41.384 --> 37:43.150
Go get 'em, tiger!

37:43.519 --> 37:47.221
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATION)

37:47.256 --> 37:48.489
(INDIE ROCK MUSIC)

37:48.524 --> 37:50.224
SIMON: Um...

37:51.427 --> 37:53.160
SIMON: Hey... what's going on?

37:53.195 --> 37:54.239
Are you giving
away free alcohol?

37:54.263 --> 37:55.607
Turns out some vampires
got wind of a singer

37:55.631 --> 37:57.364
they're really into.

37:57.400 --> 37:59.644
See? Your vampire friends know
a good thing when they see it.

37:59.668 --> 38:01.513
Something tells me it's
not all about the music.

38:01.537 --> 38:02.537
Go!

38:03.339 --> 38:04.638
I'm not letting you out of this.

38:06.542 --> 38:08.409
Oh, hey, um...

38:08.444 --> 38:09.444
this is on me.

38:11.614 --> 38:12.614
Thanks, Maia.

38:16.552 --> 38:18.385
(HIGH-PITCHED NOISE)

38:18.421 --> 38:19.253
Um...

38:19.288 --> 38:21.255
(THE CROWD GROANING)

38:21.290 --> 38:23.357
Hi! We're Rock Soli...

38:26.462 --> 38:27.528
I'm Simon Lewis.

38:28.631 --> 38:30.264
Thank you all for coming.

38:30.299 --> 38:31.331
Um...

38:33.369 --> 38:34.435
This is for the Downworld.

38:34.470 --> 38:36.537
(WHISTLING AND CHEERING)

38:36.572 --> 38:39.339
(SYNTH POP MUSIC)

38:39.375 --> 38:42.609
<i>♪</i>

38:46.382 --> 38:47.614
<i>♪ Got a drop in my throat ♪</i>

38:47.650 --> 38:49.249
<i>♪ Chill in my bones ♪</i>

38:49.285 --> 38:51.185
<i>♪ When no one's around ♪</i>

38:51.220 --> 38:52.486
<i>♪ See you lighting a flare ♪</i>

38:52.521 --> 38:54.188
<i>♪ Nobody's there ♪</i>

38:54.223 --> 38:56.290
<i>♪ They don't hear a sound ♪</i>

38:56.325 --> 38:59.159
<i>♪ Oh, the burden that I face ♪</i>

38:59.195 --> 39:00.561
<i>♪ Inside, every night ♪</i>

39:00.596 --> 39:03.497
<i>♪ I'm a stranger when I wake ♪</i>

39:03.532 --> 39:06.166
<i>♪ Wake up in your eyes ♪</i>

39:06.202 --> 39:07.568
<i>♪</i>

39:07.603 --> 39:09.236
<i>♪ When the new world ♪</i>

39:09.271 --> 39:11.505
<i>♪ I've come to know ♪</i>

39:11.540 --> 39:18.545
<i>♪ Is a replica of home ♪</i>

39:18.581 --> 39:22.316
<i>♪ Forever alone ♪</i>

39:22.351 --> 39:24.551
<i>♪</i>

39:24.587 --> 39:26.286
<i>♪ Flying, I'm a night owl ♪</i>

39:26.322 --> 39:27.387
<i>♪</i>

39:27.423 --> 39:28.703
JACE: Hey. Hey. Let me help you.

39:29.625 --> 39:33.293
MAIA: I appreciate you springing
me, but there's still

39:33.329 --> 39:34.673
a bar full of Downworlders
who might wanna gut you.

39:34.697 --> 39:36.663
Yeah, I know, but I had to come.

39:39.502 --> 39:41.368
It's to remove the chip.

39:41.403 --> 39:44.238
Direct orders from my new boss.

39:44.273 --> 39:45.439
No more tracking.

39:45.474 --> 39:46.507
<i>♪ It's a fragile world ♪</i>

39:46.542 --> 39:47.574
<i>♪ Fragile world ♪</i>

